<paragraph id="8BD336B3FF8FF93EFF3BFE4166ADFD83" blockId="75.[151,1437,417,766]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF8FF93EFF3BFE4167D4FE73" bold="true" box="[151,417,417,442]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Turreted shell; angular teleoconch whorls; rounded aperture; numerous axial riblets crossed by four spiral cords forming nodules at the intersections; spiral cord 3 (from adapical) strongest, forming pronounced angulation and periphery; non-nodulose spirals on base. Protoconch: heterostrophic, heliciform, transaxial; 2.75 whorls; diameter about 440 µm; surface smooth; transition to the teleoconch marked by a very thin varix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3766538FF8FF93EFF6BFDB567ABFD58" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FF8FF93EFF6BFDB567ABFD58" blockId="75.[151,1437,417,766]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF8FF93EFF6BFDB56726FDA7" bold="true" box="[199,339,597,622]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC05 (1 specimen), BC66 (1), BC67 (2), BC71 (11), BC72 (4); core BC51 (1). Maximum height: 
<quantity id="4C949B56FF8FF93EFE3AFD9A67AFFD58" box="[406,474,634,658]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3766538FF8FF93EFF6BFD7D6469FD37" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FF8FF93EFF6BFD7D63E7FD13" blockId="75.[151,1437,417,766]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF8FF93EFF6BFD7D679AFD7F" bold="true" box="[199,495,669,694]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D30FF8FF93EFDADFD7D64A3FD7C" authority="Semper, 1865" authorityName="Semper" authorityYear="1865" box="[513,726,669,694]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mathildidae" genus="Mathilda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="coronata">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF8FF93EFDADFD7D64A3FD7C" box="[513,726,669,694]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Mathilda coronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be endemic of the Mediterranean Sea, where it is found on bathyal soft bottoms, often in the vicinity of deep water coral banks (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FF8FF93EFBAAFD2162E3FD13" author="Kobelt" box="[1030,1174,705,730]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Kobelt, W. (1905) Iconographie der schalentragenden europaischen Meeresconchylien. Part 3. C. W. Kreidel's Verlag, Wiesbaden, 205 pp. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10278" type="book" year="1905">Kobelt 1905</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FF8FF93EFB0EFD2163F3FD13" author="Smriglio" box="[1186,1414,705,730]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Smriglio, C., Prkic, G., Di Giulio, A. &amp; Mariottini, P. (2007) Two new mathildids from the Mediterranean Sea (Gastropoda, Heterobranchia, Mathildidae). Basteria, 71 (4 - 6), 177 - 188." type="journal article" year="2007">
Smriglio 
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF8FF93EFAA7FD226336FD13" box="[1291,1347,705,730]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
